	<p class="prose">If you’re old enough, this sounds like quintessential 2000s/2010s emo: <b>Dashboard Confessional</b> lyrics over a Metro Boomin’-type beat.
	</p>
	<p class="prose">It’s already been sub-genred as emo-rap, an emerging hip hop niche of the past few years that has now dominated charts with the success of XXXtentacion and Lil Uzi Vert. But listening to Juice Wrld’s lyrics, I’d argue it is <i>emo</i>—just as emotionally vulnerable and sad as Dashboard, the poster band of mid-2000s teenage angst.
	</p>
	<p class="prose">I began to wonder: <b>who has the saddest lyrics, emo-rappers or Dashboard Confessional?</b> Has Juice Wrld found a way to out-emo emo bands?
	</p>
